Source URLs:
- https://docs.anthropic.com/en/api/getting-started
- https://docs.anthropic.com/en/api/messages-examples
- https://docs.anthropic.com/en/api/versioning
Fetched: 2026-02-27

Key requirements for direct HTTP calls:
- Endpoint for messages: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
- Required headers: x-api-key, anthropic-version, content-type: application/json
- Required version header example: anthropic-version: 2023-06-01
- Messages API is stateless; full conversation history must be sent each request.
- Request size limit for standard endpoints (messages): 32 MB.
- Response contains request-id header for tracing.

Implementation implications:
- Keep anthropic-version explicit and configurable.
- Keep x-api-key auth in every REST fallback call.
- Ensure request payload is JSON and model/max_tokens/messages are explicit.
